{
  "stem": "3524.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We saw a few of them, I found out later, that were working on binoculars, repairing them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They looked healthier.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I suspect if they had some skills they were kept working.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But most of them that we saw that were still there were just laying in these trays of human beings.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can't say that they did.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I think, at the time, there was a determination to do what you had to do.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I don't know whether it's adrenaline that takes over or what, but nobody was doing anything but the appropriate thing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't at that time.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I did take a number of pictures because I wanted to document this for people whom I'm sure wouldn't believe it if they were told the visual description of it.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This-- you got used to it after a couple days, but the smells were indescribable.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] one of the fellows described it as just the smell of death.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were, of course, lots of diarrhea, human fecal material around, but there was another odd, almost indescribable odor to the whole place.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I only wrote one to my brother describing the things because I didn't feel that I was adequate to talk to anybody else who would understand it.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I got a view of the kitchen, and all I could see was the bread that they were baking.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They did have bread there, and they were in the process of distributing some pieces of bread to the various prisoners.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, most of them were able to feed-- be fed-- but a good share of them couldn't take any solid food until after intravenous products were given.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the camp was on a hill, and it was a beautiful sight.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
